y of various places called Seaton, such as those in Cumberland, Devon, Durham, Leicestershire, Northumberland, Rutland, East Yorkshire, and North Yorkshire, most of which derive from Old English <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea, lake’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though the Leicestershire placename probably arises from an Old English personal name <i>Sǣga</i> or a stream-name <i>Sǣge</i> (from Old English <i>sǣge</i> ‘slow moving’; compare   Seabrook  ) + Old English <i>tūn</i>.","Scottish: habitational name from Seton (East Lothian), from Old English <i>sǣ</i> ‘sea’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Seton was born about 1395, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Erskine. She died in 1479, at the age of 85."},"et":{"Abt 1395–1479":"umbes 1395–1479","1395–Male":"1395–Surnud","1411–1445":"1411–1445","1395–1479":"1395–1479","Abt 1395":"umbes 1395","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1411":"1411","14 July 1445":"14. juuli 1445","1395":"1395","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Perth, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1395–1479":"noin 1395–1479","1395–Male":"1395–Kuollut","1411–1445":"1411–1445","1395–1479":"1395–1479","Abt 1395":"noin 1395","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1411":"1411","14 July 1445":"14. heinäkuuta 1445","1395":"1395","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dumfriesshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Perth, Perthshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1395–1479":"environ 1395–1479","1395–Male":"1395–Décédé","1411–1445":"1411–1445","1395–1479":"1395–1479","Abt 1395":"environ 1395","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1411":"1411","14 July 1445":"14 juillet 1445","1395":"1395","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dumfriesshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Perth, Perthshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Seton est née environ 1395, à Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Erskine. Elle est décédée en 1479, à l’âge de 85 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1395–1479":"um 1395–1479","1395–Male":"1395–Verstorben","1411–1445":"1411–1445","1395–1479":"1395–1479","Abt 1395":"um 1395","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1411":"1411","14 July 1445":"14. Juli 1445","1395":"1395","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Schottland, United Kingdom","Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dumfriesshire, Sch